<c74object name='dk.avdog~' category='' module='dataknot'>
    <digest>AVDog-inspired synth voice
</digest>
    <description>The <o>dk.avdog~</o> object is a digital recreation of the AVDog in the ciat-lonbarde Plumbutter drum and drama machine. The AVDog &quot;takes a pulse and undulates at human brain waves, thus creating a meta-resonance, which is manifested as the envelope of a synthesized electronic tone&quot;. It is essentially a self-oscillating SVF filter which can be pinged to create sustained/throbbing pitches.
</description>
    <discussion>Based on the ciat-lonbarde Plumbutter drum and drama machine. For more information visit <a href="https://ciat-lonbarde.net/ciat-lonbarde/plumbutter/index.html">https://ciat-lonbarde.net/ciat-lonbarde/plumbutter/index.html</a>
</discussion>

	<metadatalist>
		<metadata name='author'>Rodrigo Constanzo, FluCoMa Project</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Machine Learning</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Audio Analysis</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Onset Detection</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Corpus Playback</metadata>
	</metadatalist>

